<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-454-886  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 454 886.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  July 24 1989 n548 p50(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Diversity yields recovery at Adaptec. (Adaptec Inc. )andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wirbel, Loring.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Adaptec Inc has recovered from diminishing revenues in 1988 byoffering a diverse product line - beyond its Small ComputerSystems Interface (SCSI) boards and cards.andP;  Adaptec was a pioneerin building and promoting the SCSI interface.andP;  However, thecompany opted to expand its operations beyond SCSI after facingmore intense competition.andP;  It now has four separate divisions,storage products operation, communications products operation,peripheral products operation and development systems operations.andO;The latter operation is the fastest growing, attracting more than$10 million in revenue out of $64.7 million corporate total.andO;Development systems for SCSI peripherals are in demand and thereare few sources outside of Adaptec participating in the market.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Adaptec Inc. (finance).andO;Ticker:    ADPT.andO;Topic:     Boards-CardsSmall Computer Systems InterfaceDiversificationFinancial StabilityProduct DevelopmentExpansionMarket PenetrationGrowth.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>